commitResults.messageBody:
Enable automatic saving and loading of internships to maintain data between application restarts.
Data is stored in pipe-delimited format (company | role | deadline | pay | status) at ./data/internships.txt with automatic parent directory creation.

Features:
- Auto-save after each command execution in main REPL loop
- Auto-load on application startup
- Graceful degradation: corrupted lines are skipped with warnings
- Robust error handling with InternityException for I/O failures

Storage class implementation:
- load(): Reads internships from file, handles missing file (first run)
- save(): Writes internships to file, creates directories if needed
- parseInternshipFromFile(): Parses pipe-delimited lines with validation
- formatInternshipForFile(): Formats internships for file storage
- Logging at INFO, WARNING, and SEVERE levels for debugging
- Assertions on all public methods

InternshipList updates:
- Add setStorage() to configure storage instance
- Add loadFromStorage() to populate list from file
- Add saveToStorage() to persist current state

Internity updates:
- Initialize Storage in initInternity()
- Load data on startup with error handling
- Auto-save after each successful command execution
